    <para id="para-00012">Because the last column is true for every entry, the biconditional is valid and the statement <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></math> is logically equivalent to the statement <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mrow><mo>~</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>∨</mo><mi>q</mi></mrow></math>. Symbolically, <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>q</mi><mtext> </mtext><mo>≡</mo><mtext> </mtext><mo>~</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>∨</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></math></para>
